1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:50,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:53,371 --> 00:00:55,197
Are you okay?

3
00:00:56,023 --> 00:00:59,443
Your fever went up to
39 degrees Celsius overnight.

4
00:00:59,443 --> 00:01:00,920
Still sick?

5
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:03,013
Do you want to go to the hospital?

6
00:01:04,983 --> 00:01:07,059
Why were you so late?

7
00:01:09,887 --> 00:01:12,223
You know I hate

8
00:01:12,223 --> 00:01:14,316
waiting for someone.

9
00:01:17,854 --> 00:01:19,738
Sun Tae Hyung...

10
00:01:21,858 --> 00:01:23,617
I like you.

11
00:01:24,777 --> 00:01:26,453
Woo Hyun Jin.

12
00:01:29,724 --> 00:01:32,518
That's why I keep finding myself
waiting for you.

13
00:01:34,746 --> 00:01:38,715
You're my first everything.

14
00:01:40,626 --> 00:01:43,971
No one's ever waited up for me,

15
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:47,658
or come home when I waited for them...

16
00:02:06,361 --> 00:02:08,537
I think someone's at the door.

17
00:02:14,435 --> 00:02:15,453
No, it's fine.

18
00:02:15,453 --> 00:02:17,747
It's heavy, let me get that.

19
00:02:17,747 --> 00:02:19,482
Here, hold this.

20
00:02:19,482 --> 00:02:20,667
Where did all this come from?

21
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:23,962
Just some side dishes, no big deal.

22
00:02:23,962 --> 00:02:25,463
Some greens and dried veggies, nothing fancy.

23
00:02:25,463 --> 00:02:26,506
You need to eat right if you're raising a kid.

24
00:02:26,506 --> 00:02:27,990
You really didn't have to...

25
00:02:27,990 --> 00:02:29,467
My mom's getting old, you know,

26
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:32,119
so she always makes way too much. Well then,

27
00:02:32,119 --> 00:02:34,498
I'll just toss it then. Hand it over.

28
00:02:34,498 --> 00:02:35,537
Wait, no.

29
00:02:35,537 --> 00:02:36,999
I'll eat it all. Thank you so much.

30
00:02:36,999 --> 00:02:38,459
I'll return the containers empty.

31
00:02:38,459 --> 00:02:41,045
Oh, that would be lovely.

32
00:02:41,045 --> 00:02:42,689
Is little Woo Joo asleep?

33
00:02:42,689 --> 00:02:44,482
Oh my, he is.

34
00:02:44,482 --> 00:02:46,659
I better keep it down.

35
00:02:47,777 --> 00:02:49,929
Can you see through those things?

36
00:02:49,929 --> 00:02:51,013
What's with the sunglasses indoors...

37
00:02:51,013 --> 00:02:53,015
Oh, never mind that.

38
00:02:53,015 --> 00:02:54,367
So Bom's mom told me...

39
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:57,586
you two aren't a couple, but in-laws?

40
00:03:00,457 --> 00:03:04,218
This villa has zero secrets, I swear.

41
00:03:09,991 --> 00:03:12,744
What's the deal with you two?

42
00:03:13,737 --> 00:03:14,763
No.

43
00:03:14,763 --> 00:03:16,264
Then what's with all this tension?

44
00:03:16,264 --> 00:03:18,016
There's something I wanted to ask you.

45
00:03:18,016 --> 00:03:19,184
- Something went down, right?
- You'll wake Woo Joo up.

46
00:03:19,184 --> 00:03:22,896
He keeps shushing me and telling me to zip it.

47
00:03:22,896 --> 00:03:24,564
Something definitely happened, right?

48
00:03:24,564 --> 00:03:26,306
Right?

49
00:03:30,987 --> 00:03:32,409
Gosh.

50
00:03:32,409 --> 00:03:35,190
Did I really just say all that
looking like this?

51
00:03:44,275 --> 00:03:47,334
[Episode 6]

52
00:03:55,119 --> 00:03:58,372
You should at least sleep properly.

53
00:04:32,698 --> 00:04:36,494
You should've told me not to go
if you're this sick...

54
00:04:41,391 --> 00:04:44,151
Even when I ask people to stay,

55
00:04:44,772 --> 00:04:47,154
they all leave anyway.

56
00:04:52,802 --> 00:04:55,204
I'm not going anywhere.

57
00:05:19,412 --> 00:05:21,539
Thanks for coming.

58
00:05:39,897 --> 00:05:42,209
You're up already?

59
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:45,646
You alright? Did you burn your tongue?

60
00:05:54,881 --> 00:05:56,574
It's nothing.

61
00:05:56,574 --> 00:05:57,992
I need to leave for work soon.

62
00:05:57,992 --> 00:05:59,511
Let me go get ready.

63
00:05:59,511 --> 00:06:01,763
You hardly got any sleep, right?

64
00:06:01,763 --> 00:06:02,788
No, it's okay.

65
00:06:02,788 --> 00:06:04,557
Whenever your temperature went up overnight,

66
00:06:04,557 --> 00:06:05,809
I caught some sleep in between.

67
00:06:05,809 --> 00:06:08,311
I left some porridge for you, so eat up.

68
00:06:08,311 --> 00:06:09,871
And before you head out,

69
00:06:09,871 --> 00:06:11,064
if you take Woo Joo over to Bom's,

70
00:06:11,064 --> 00:06:12,607
I'll grab him on my way back.

71
00:06:12,607 --> 00:06:13,716
One more thing...

72
00:06:13,716 --> 00:06:15,076
Have you eaten?

73
00:06:15,076 --> 00:06:16,093
What?

74
00:06:16,093 --> 00:06:18,012
I asked if you had eaten.

75
00:06:18,905 --> 00:06:21,408
No, I'll grab something at the office.

76
00:06:21,408 --> 00:06:22,534
I should get going.

77
00:06:22,534 --> 00:06:24,251
Woo Joo, bye.

78
00:06:38,532 --> 00:06:40,385
I like you.

79
00:06:40,385 --> 00:06:42,186
Woo Hyun Jin.

80
00:06:44,497 --> 00:06:47,208
Why is my heart beating so fast?

81
00:06:52,051 --> 00:06:53,064
Hello?

82
00:06:53,064 --> 00:06:55,299
Is this the guardian of Sun Woo Joo?

83
00:06:55,299 --> 00:06:57,676
Yes, that's me. What's going on?

84
00:06:57,676 --> 00:06:59,946
Hi, I'm calling from Saetbyeol Daycare.

85
00:06:59,946 --> 00:07:01,114
We have an opening now

86
00:07:01,114 --> 00:07:03,074
in our infant class and wanted to let you know.

87
00:07:03,074 --> 00:07:04,576
Oh, that's wonderful!

88
00:07:04,576 --> 00:07:06,286
How soon can he come in?

89
00:07:06,286 --> 00:07:08,163
If it's convenient for you,

90
00:07:08,163 --> 00:07:09,980
he's welcome to come in today.

91
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:12,750
Even if it's later in the day, stop by
so he can meet the other children

92
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:15,044
and start getting comfortable.

93
00:07:15,044 --> 00:07:16,379
Sure, that works.

94
00:07:16,379 --> 00:07:17,947
I'll plan on that.

95
00:07:17,947 --> 00:07:19,507
I really appreciate it.

96
00:07:19,507 --> 00:07:21,350
Thank you.

97
00:07:22,326 --> 00:07:24,662
I need to tell Tae Hyung about this.

98
00:07:26,372 --> 00:07:27,798
Actually, hold on.

99
00:07:27,798 --> 00:07:30,609
Is it too soon to call right now?

100
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:43,539
You literally just ate.

101
00:07:45,734 --> 00:07:48,919
Those puppy eyes are not going to work.

102
00:07:54,423 --> 00:07:56,294
This has never happened to me before.

103
00:07:56,294 --> 00:07:59,763
Someone making me porridge when I'm sick.

104
00:08:04,744 --> 00:08:08,080
Wait, did she leave without eating

105
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,333
just because of me?

106
00:08:12,727 --> 00:08:15,321
- Really?
- Yeah.

107
00:08:16,689 --> 00:08:19,491
Is it that hard to be around me?

108
00:08:23,756 --> 00:08:26,155
Would you mind taking Woo Joo

109
00:08:26,155 --> 00:08:28,284
to daycare before work today?

110
00:08:28,284 --> 00:08:29,781
Daycare?

111
00:08:29,781 --> 00:08:32,489
I signed Woo Joo up for a waitlist before,

112
00:08:32,489 --> 00:08:34,148
and they just called saying a spot's open.

113
00:08:34,148 --> 00:08:36,116
I'll send you the address.

114
00:08:38,277 --> 00:08:41,364
He's still a baby, not a kid.

115
00:08:45,393 --> 00:08:48,012
Alright, time to get dressed.

116
00:08:48,012 --> 00:08:48,596
No!

117
00:08:48,596 --> 00:08:50,139
Give me your foot.

118
00:08:50,139 --> 00:08:51,832
No.

119
00:08:51,832 --> 00:08:53,709
Alright.

120
00:08:56,437 --> 00:08:59,448
It took 30 minutes just to get dressed?

121
00:09:07,348 --> 00:09:09,242
Okay, I'll go grab that.

122
00:09:09,242 --> 00:09:11,585
Wait.

123
00:09:22,655 --> 00:09:25,321
This place is bigger than I expected.

124
00:09:25,321 --> 00:09:28,219
[Nice to meet you! Welcome!]
You'll be fine, right?

125
00:09:28,219 --> 00:09:30,229
- Yeah.
- Really?

126
00:09:30,913 --> 00:09:32,557
Alright.

127
00:09:32,557 --> 00:09:34,892
Let's head inside.

128
00:09:34,892 --> 00:09:36,144
You're Woo Joo, right?

129
00:09:36,144 --> 00:09:37,353
Hello.

130
00:09:37,353 --> 00:09:38,605
- Say hello.
- Come on, bow.

131
00:09:38,605 --> 00:09:39,897
Hands on your belly, just like that.

132
00:09:39,897 --> 00:09:41,573
Come on.

133
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,760
[Saetbyeol Daycare]

134
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,155
Would you happen to be Woo Joo's dad?

135
00:09:47,155 --> 00:09:48,956
His dad?

136
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:51,409
Where do you see...

137
00:09:51,409 --> 00:09:54,002
I'm just the uncle.

138
00:09:55,907 --> 00:09:57,081
Got it.

139
00:09:57,081 --> 00:09:59,066
You do give off that uncle vibe, honestly.

140
00:09:59,066 --> 00:10:00,752
Well then,

141
00:10:00,752 --> 00:10:03,720
could you jot down an emergency contact?

142
00:10:08,659 --> 00:10:11,002
[Saetbyeol Daycare Emergency Contact]

143
00:10:17,876 --> 00:10:20,671
[Child's Name: Sun Woo Joo]

144
00:10:20,671 --> 00:10:23,598
[Guardian of Sun Woo Joo, Sun Tae Hyung]

145
00:10:46,255 --> 00:10:47,865
Excuse me.

146
00:10:47,865 --> 00:10:49,384
One thing before you go,

147
00:10:49,384 --> 00:10:51,052
tell him something like, "Uncle has to work,

148
00:10:51,052 --> 00:10:52,512
but you play with your friends here,

149
00:10:52,512 --> 00:10:53,429
and I'll be back for you soon."

150
00:10:53,429 --> 00:10:54,972
Make sure you say that before you leave.

151
00:10:54,972 --> 00:10:56,766
That way he's not left
wondering when you'll come back,

152
00:10:56,766 --> 00:10:57,975
he won't feel anxious,

153
00:10:57,975 --> 00:11:00,144
and it gives him a sense of comfort

154
00:11:00,144 --> 00:11:02,629
knowing you will be back for him.

155
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:04,424
Sure.

156
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,017
Right.

157
00:11:40,017 --> 00:11:42,444
He shouldn't be left waiting
without knowing when.

158
00:11:49,277 --> 00:11:52,162
Uncle.

159
00:11:58,536 --> 00:12:00,796
- Hey.
- Yeah.

160
00:12:05,405 --> 00:12:07,271
Woo Joo.

161
00:12:09,213 --> 00:12:13,478
I need to go earn some money
for your meals and diapers, alright?

162
00:12:15,803 --> 00:12:18,264
So,

163
00:12:18,264 --> 00:12:21,017
hang out here and play with your friends.

164
00:12:22,251 --> 00:12:24,426
And then Auntie will come get you.

165
00:12:24,426 --> 00:12:25,438
Okay?

166
00:12:26,088 --> 00:12:27,882
High five.

167
00:13:13,809 --> 00:13:15,929
What is this?

168
00:13:15,929 --> 00:13:18,641
This weirdly empty feeling.

169
00:13:23,228 --> 00:13:25,982
I forgot to give her an update.

170
00:13:26,887 --> 00:13:29,951
Woo Joo's all bathed and changed,

171
00:13:30,947 --> 00:13:35,665
and his first day of daycare is a wrap.

172
00:13:37,552 --> 00:13:39,752
Guess I should send her a picture, too.

173
00:13:40,847 --> 00:13:42,643
This one?

174
00:13:44,934 --> 00:13:46,185
What the...

175
00:13:46,185 --> 00:13:46,894
What did I just do?

176
00:13:46,894 --> 00:13:48,229
No, no.

177
00:13:48,229 --> 00:13:50,857
How do I unsend this?

178
00:13:50,857 --> 00:13:53,294
Too late, she saw it.

179
00:13:53,294 --> 00:13:55,344
What is this?

180
00:13:55,344 --> 00:13:57,512
What's wrong?

181
00:13:57,512 --> 00:13:59,448
What's going on with you two?

182
00:13:59,448 --> 00:14:02,001
Have you been exchanging selfies

183
00:14:02,001 --> 00:14:03,369
without telling me?

184
00:14:03,369 --> 00:14:06,171
So something else went down, right?

185
00:14:06,856 --> 00:14:09,066
Well, the truth is...

186
00:14:09,066 --> 00:14:11,276
Someone told me they like me.

187
00:14:11,276 --> 00:14:12,336
Are you serious?

188
00:14:12,336 --> 00:14:13,546
He confessed?

189
00:14:13,546 --> 00:14:14,797
He did that?

190
00:14:14,797 --> 00:14:16,966
Since when did things speed up like this?

191
00:14:16,966 --> 00:14:18,259
Give me all the details.

192
00:14:18,259 --> 00:14:20,303
And what was your reaction?

193
00:14:20,303 --> 00:14:23,097
He was probably just out of it from the meds.

194
00:14:23,097 --> 00:14:25,315
His fever was through the roof yesterday.

195
00:14:26,017 --> 00:14:28,085
That's not my question.

196
00:14:28,085 --> 00:14:30,338
I'm asking about your feelings.

197
00:14:32,297 --> 00:14:33,691
Think about it,

198
00:14:33,691 --> 00:14:35,943
if you run into your first love again,

199
00:14:35,943 --> 00:14:38,654
wouldn't old feelings come back?

200
00:14:38,654 --> 00:14:41,014
That senior was your first love, right?

201
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:43,951
Yeah, he was.

202
00:14:43,951 --> 00:14:45,852
And judging by how he treats you,

203
00:14:45,852 --> 00:14:48,856
he clearly still cares about you.

204
00:14:50,188 --> 00:14:51,959
Honestly, I can't tell.

205
00:14:51,959 --> 00:14:53,294
He's always been kind

206
00:14:53,294 --> 00:14:55,296
and considerate with everyone.

207
00:14:55,296 --> 00:14:56,839
Oh, come on.

208
00:14:56,839 --> 00:14:59,474
I bet it's just you he treats that way.

209
00:15:00,553 --> 00:15:02,637
And what about your in-law?

210
00:15:02,637 --> 00:15:04,138
Has he ever made you feel

211
00:15:04,138 --> 00:15:07,516
something different?

212
00:15:07,516 --> 00:15:09,443
Something different?

213
00:15:10,043 --> 00:15:12,721
I mean, if you put it that way...

214
00:15:14,637 --> 00:15:16,283
Hyun Jin...

215
00:15:17,676 --> 00:15:19,886
There have been moments, yeah.

216
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:22,406
He appears when I least expect it

217
00:15:22,406 --> 00:15:24,975
and catches me off guard,

218
00:15:24,975 --> 00:15:28,062
and I find myself depending on him.

219
00:15:29,830 --> 00:15:31,631
Plus,

220
00:15:33,668 --> 00:15:37,345
he had his guard up at first, so I missed it,

221
00:15:38,411 --> 00:15:40,341
but deep down, he cares more than most

222
00:15:40,341 --> 00:15:42,642
and he's been through a lot.

223
00:15:44,411 --> 00:15:47,373
Once I saw that, it all made sense.

224
00:15:48,123 --> 00:15:49,458
I realized

225
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:52,003
he's been lonely this whole time.

226
00:15:53,229 --> 00:15:54,504
And it hit me that

227
00:15:54,504 --> 00:15:57,258
we might be pretty similar.

228
00:15:59,218 --> 00:16:01,070
If you're thinking about him that much,

229
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:02,435
then just say yes.

230
00:16:02,435 --> 00:16:03,388
What's holding you back?

231
00:16:03,388 --> 00:16:04,765
There is a problem.

232
00:16:04,765 --> 00:16:07,267
I've never once seen him that way.

233
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:10,579
Then try looking at him differently.

234
00:16:10,579 --> 00:16:12,456
Seriously, you share a place

235
00:16:12,456 --> 00:16:13,541
with a man who has feelings for you,

236
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:15,079
and you don't feel a single thing?

237
00:16:15,079 --> 00:16:17,302
How is that even possible?

238
00:16:18,111 --> 00:16:21,323
Unless your heart's already with your senior.

239
00:16:21,323 --> 00:16:23,159
My heart?

240
00:16:24,660 --> 00:16:27,000
All I have room for right now is...

241
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,502
Woo Joo and landing a full-time job.

242
00:16:33,502 --> 00:16:35,921
Those two things, that's it.

243
00:16:35,921 --> 00:16:36,939
You know that

244
00:16:36,939 --> 00:16:39,567
I can't afford to think
about anything else right now.

245
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:40,592
I don't know about that.

246
00:16:40,592 --> 00:16:44,097
I think time will tell.

247
00:16:50,519 --> 00:16:53,581
[Woo Joo's all bathed and changed,
and his first day of daycare is a wrap.]

248
00:16:53,581 --> 00:16:56,091
She read it and didn't even reply?

249
00:16:58,568 --> 00:17:00,738
Let's just focus on work.

250
00:17:02,618 --> 00:17:04,224
Shall we head in?

251
00:17:05,742 --> 00:17:07,178
[Food Supply Overview]
We have direct deals

252
00:17:07,178 --> 00:17:08,620
with quality-verified suppliers

253
00:17:08,620 --> 00:17:10,765
along with several
alternative sources in place.

254
00:17:10,765 --> 00:17:12,224
That's great.

255
00:17:12,224 --> 00:17:15,561
GloMarket took interest in the K-food brand

256
00:17:15,561 --> 00:17:17,087
that's been developed with care over the years,

257
00:17:17,087 --> 00:17:19,102
which means we absolutely must secure

258
00:17:19,102 --> 00:17:20,483
top-tier raw materials.

259
00:17:20,483 --> 00:17:22,631
Of course, we'll make it happen.

260
00:17:22,631 --> 00:17:26,155
Let's call it a day on this meeting, then?

261
00:17:26,155 --> 00:17:28,039
Thank you all.

262
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:37,215
The roads will be packed at this hour.

263
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:39,168
Tell me about it.

264
00:17:39,168 --> 00:17:40,336
So I was thinking...

265
00:17:40,336 --> 00:17:42,345
What if we sneak off for a bit?

266
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:50,971
Can we order?

267
00:17:50,971 --> 00:17:52,539
Sure, go right ahead.

268
00:17:52,539 --> 00:17:55,125
One Strawberry Love Latte, extra whip,

269
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:56,977
five rounds of java chips blended on top,

270
00:17:56,977 --> 00:17:58,437
with tons of chocolate drizzle,

271
00:17:58,437 --> 00:18:00,782
and finish it off with banana pudding.

272
00:18:00,782 --> 00:18:01,816
I'm sorry?

273
00:18:01,816 --> 00:18:03,575
Banana pudding.

274
00:18:06,303 --> 00:18:07,913
What is this?

275
00:18:07,913 --> 00:18:08,930
What else could it be?

276
00:18:08,930 --> 00:18:11,392
It's your signature order.

277
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:14,370
I can't believe you still know that.

278
00:18:14,370 --> 00:18:16,396
How could I forget?

279
00:18:16,396 --> 00:18:18,415
They only have this latte during the season.

280
00:18:18,415 --> 00:18:19,708
So each year when it comes back,

281
00:18:19,708 --> 00:18:22,294
I'd walk by and you'd cross my mind.

282
00:18:22,294 --> 00:18:24,571
Whenever I'd see someone with one,

283
00:18:24,571 --> 00:18:27,086
I'd wonder if you'd had yours yet.

284
00:18:27,086 --> 00:18:30,035
And when it disappeared from the menu,

285
00:18:30,035 --> 00:18:31,954
I'd feel this little pang of sadness.

286
00:18:32,579 --> 00:18:35,541
That's why everyone falls for you.

287
00:18:36,372 --> 00:18:40,866
I haven't had a single girlfriend
since college.

288
00:18:40,866 --> 00:18:41,922
Come on.

289
00:18:41,922 --> 00:18:44,030
What? I mean it.

290
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:44,999
Why is that so hard to believe?

291
00:18:44,999 --> 00:18:48,678
It's just, you've always been well-liked,

292
00:18:48,678 --> 00:18:52,015
clearly brilliant, capable, kind,

293
00:18:52,015 --> 00:18:54,852
and on top of it all, tall and handso...

294
00:18:56,745 --> 00:18:58,813
Go on?

295
00:18:58,813 --> 00:19:01,067
Why'd you trail off?

296
00:19:02,150 --> 00:19:03,502
Because you keep messing with me,

297
00:19:03,502 --> 00:19:06,748
I say things I don't mean to.

298
00:19:09,508 --> 00:19:11,088
By the way.

299
00:19:11,088 --> 00:19:13,220
How's the little one?

300
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:14,287
He's good.

301
00:19:14,287 --> 00:19:16,469
He went to daycare for the first time today.

302
00:19:16,469 --> 00:19:17,499
He's all grown up, right?

303
00:19:17,499 --> 00:19:20,543
He really is.

304
00:19:20,543 --> 00:19:23,046
Now that must be a relief.

305
00:19:23,046 --> 00:19:24,690
It really is.

306
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:26,901
I was stressing about managing

307
00:19:26,901 --> 00:19:29,431
without my in-law around.

308
00:19:29,431 --> 00:19:33,329
You're not living with your in-law anymore?

309
00:19:33,329 --> 00:19:37,544
We only planned on staying together
for a month to begin with.

310
00:19:39,496 --> 00:19:41,255
I'm glad to hear that.

311
00:19:42,332 --> 00:19:43,399
What do you mean?

312
00:19:43,399 --> 00:19:45,994
Honestly, it made me a little uneasy,

313
00:19:46,628 --> 00:19:49,347
knowing you were staying with a man.

314
00:20:00,976 --> 00:20:03,211
Here's the thing about Amy Choo.

315
00:20:03,211 --> 00:20:07,323
She hates being disturbed
when inspiration strikes.

316
00:20:08,066 --> 00:20:10,485
So if she doesn't respond,

317
00:20:10,485 --> 00:20:13,906
it means something big is forming in her head,

318
00:20:13,906 --> 00:20:15,873
so give her space.

319
00:20:17,201 --> 00:20:18,433
As for storyboarding,

320
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:20,579
she does it all by hand first.

321
00:20:20,579 --> 00:20:22,122
Typing it all up afterward,

322
00:20:22,122 --> 00:20:24,441
that falls on you.

323
00:20:24,441 --> 00:20:26,675
When creative differences come up,

324
00:20:26,675 --> 00:20:28,629
she leads with profanity,

325
00:20:28,629 --> 00:20:31,764
and you'll be the one who has to manage that.

326
00:20:32,615 --> 00:20:35,289
Sets, talent, styling,

327
00:20:35,289 --> 00:20:37,137
without needing step-by-step instructions,

328
00:20:37,137 --> 00:20:39,372
you figure it all out yourself,

329
00:20:39,372 --> 00:20:42,996
clean and with sharp instincts.

330
00:20:42,996 --> 00:20:44,002
Most importantly,

331
00:20:44,002 --> 00:20:47,022
she's very particular about what she eats,

332
00:20:47,022 --> 00:20:50,359
so it all has to be organic.

333
00:20:50,359 --> 00:20:52,319
Half an hour after each meal,

334
00:20:52,319 --> 00:20:58,166
hand her vitamins A, B, C, D, E

335
00:20:59,718 --> 00:21:01,620
on a rotating schedule,

336
00:21:01,620 --> 00:21:03,205
and supplement the rest with fruit...

337
00:21:03,205 --> 00:21:04,915
Hold on,

338
00:21:04,915 --> 00:21:08,468
wasn't I hired to be an assistant?

339
00:21:09,743 --> 00:21:10,754
That's correct.

340
00:21:10,754 --> 00:21:12,172
And I'm expected to do all that?

341
00:21:12,172 --> 00:21:13,006
By myself?

342
00:21:13,006 --> 00:21:15,391
Is that too much for you?

343
00:21:16,093 --> 00:21:17,994
I can handle it, absolutely.

344
00:21:17,994 --> 00:21:19,763
Whatever needs to be done, I'll do it.

345
00:21:19,763 --> 00:21:20,681
That's what I like to hear.

346
00:21:20,681 --> 00:21:23,189
This is Amy Choo's team we're talking about.

347
00:21:23,189 --> 00:21:24,214
Just so you know,

348
00:21:24,214 --> 00:21:25,769
if your plan is to slack off for a while

349
00:21:25,769 --> 00:21:27,896
and use Amy Choo's reputation

350
00:21:27,896 --> 00:21:29,314
as a stepping stone for yourself...

351
00:21:29,314 --> 00:21:30,983
I wouldn't have taken the job.

352
00:21:30,983 --> 00:21:33,659
For me, this role is

353
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:39,241
my final chance too.

354
00:21:39,241 --> 00:21:41,417
Then we're on the same page.

355
00:21:41,417 --> 00:21:42,435
Oh, one more thing.

356
00:21:42,435 --> 00:21:44,020
Did you get through

357
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:45,706
that proposal Amy Choo asked you to check?

358
00:21:45,706 --> 00:21:47,102
I'm working through it now,

359
00:21:47,102 --> 00:21:48,166
but the visual references still

360
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:51,211
need some more cross-referencing,

361
00:21:51,211 --> 00:21:53,655
so I'll wrap it up and report back
by end of day.

362
00:21:53,655 --> 00:21:55,700
I love

363
00:21:56,878 --> 00:21:58,768
that attitude.

364
00:22:00,262 --> 00:22:02,980
She needs her coffee right about now.

365
00:22:04,016 --> 00:22:05,976
I have to go.

366
00:22:05,976 --> 00:22:07,985
I'm late.

367
00:22:10,605 --> 00:22:14,200
He's so devoted to her.

368
00:22:16,194 --> 00:22:18,037
There's so much on my plate.

369
00:22:26,121 --> 00:22:27,964
One, two.

370
00:22:30,709 --> 00:22:32,336
Give me something bashful, bashful.

371
00:22:32,336 --> 00:22:34,095
There it is, bashful.

372
00:22:36,214 --> 00:22:39,016
Now the look on your face, light and airy.

373
00:22:43,722 --> 00:22:45,724
Hang on a second.

374
00:22:45,724 --> 00:22:48,317
He told me he'd only worked as an assistant.

375
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,672
These shots are actually impressive.

376
00:22:58,987 --> 00:23:00,955
You finished it all.

377
00:23:03,766 --> 00:23:04,910
[My Daily Life]

378
00:23:04,910 --> 00:23:08,497
I thought maybe I sent him too soon,

379
00:23:08,497 --> 00:23:11,424
but he did great on his own.

380
00:23:12,632 --> 00:23:15,420
I feel like I've barely done anything,

381
00:23:15,420 --> 00:23:17,805
yet here he is, growing up so fast.

382
00:23:19,299 --> 00:23:20,717
Woo Joo.

383
00:23:20,717 --> 00:23:22,118
Was daycare fun today?

384
00:23:23,282 --> 00:23:26,932
Think you can do it again tomorrow?

385
00:23:29,601 --> 00:23:30,936
Where are you going?

386
00:23:30,936 --> 00:23:32,695
Woo Joo, where are you going?

387
00:23:36,775 --> 00:23:38,360
You're back?

388
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:40,320
Yeah, I'm back.

389
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,780
Woo Joo's here too?

390
00:23:42,989 --> 00:23:45,412
I grabbed him on my way back from work.

391
00:23:45,412 --> 00:23:46,910
I see.

392
00:23:46,910 --> 00:23:47,994
Did you eat yet?

393
00:23:47,994 --> 00:23:49,712
Yeah, I ate.

394
00:23:50,622 --> 00:23:52,332
Oh, great. Good.

395
00:23:52,332 --> 00:23:54,376
- Let me start the laund...
- It's already done.

396
00:23:54,376 --> 00:23:56,128
Don't worry about it.

397
00:23:56,128 --> 00:23:58,004
Oh, really?

398
00:23:58,004 --> 00:23:59,047
I bet we were low on detergent...

399
00:23:59,047 --> 00:24:01,891
So I grabbed some on the way back.

400
00:24:07,931 --> 00:24:10,225
Honestly,

401
00:24:10,225 --> 00:24:11,268
how do I put this,

402
00:24:11,268 --> 00:24:12,853
you're amazing, truly amazing.

403
00:24:14,003 --> 00:24:15,840
Thank you.

404
00:24:16,565 --> 00:24:17,899
Really, thank you.

405
00:24:17,899 --> 00:24:19,669
Woo Joo, Auntie's the best, right?

406
00:24:22,696 --> 00:24:24,072
Let me just hit the bathroom.

407
00:24:24,072 --> 00:24:25,449
Yeah, have a good...

408
00:24:25,449 --> 00:24:27,291
Take care.

409
00:24:33,206 --> 00:24:36,008
Did I just say "have a good trip"?

410
00:24:42,674 --> 00:24:45,302
I really

411
00:24:45,302 --> 00:24:47,679
need to fix this.

412
00:24:47,679 --> 00:24:49,313
Woo Joo, bye.

413
00:24:50,474 --> 00:24:52,400
Let me just hit the bathroom.

414
00:25:04,529 --> 00:25:05,530
Hello?

415
00:25:05,530 --> 00:25:06,865
Hello.

416
00:25:06,865 --> 00:25:08,582
Oh, right.

417
00:25:10,619 --> 00:25:12,211
Yes.

418
00:25:12,954 --> 00:25:14,289
Yes.

419
00:25:14,289 --> 00:25:17,209
What's with all the "yes, yes"?

420
00:25:17,209 --> 00:25:18,293
Excuse me.

421
00:25:18,293 --> 00:25:20,837
The repairs at your apartment are finished.

422
00:25:20,837 --> 00:25:22,214
Everything's been fixed up,

423
00:25:22,214 --> 00:25:24,466
so come take a look, and if it checks out,

424
00:25:24,466 --> 00:25:26,551
you can move back in immediately.

425
00:25:26,551 --> 00:25:27,552
By the way,

426
00:25:27,552 --> 00:25:30,597
how did you get it done so quickly?

427
00:25:30,597 --> 00:25:32,265
Is it even done properly?

428
00:25:32,265 --> 00:25:33,391
You were the one

429
00:25:33,391 --> 00:25:35,185
who kept asking me to hurry up, remember?

430
00:25:35,185 --> 00:25:37,354
Plus, it's almost been a month already,

431
00:25:37,354 --> 00:25:38,980
so I'm not sure what the issue is.

432
00:25:38,980 --> 00:25:41,782
Alright, I'll stop by and see it tomorrow.

433
00:25:48,389 --> 00:25:51,826
[The Day I Go Home]

434
00:25:51,826 --> 00:25:54,645
Has it really been a whole month already?

435
00:25:54,645 --> 00:25:57,157
Where did all the time go?

436
00:26:05,506 --> 00:26:09,164
I'm fine doing this on my own.

437
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:15,212
I was serious.

438
00:26:18,586 --> 00:26:21,131
What I told you,

439
00:26:21,131 --> 00:26:23,678
all of it was real.

440
00:26:25,756 --> 00:26:27,967
However,

441
00:26:27,967 --> 00:26:29,135
I won't

442
00:26:29,135 --> 00:26:31,395
expect anything from you.

443
00:26:32,555 --> 00:26:35,349
I just wanted you to know where I stand.

444
00:26:35,349 --> 00:26:38,394
I'm not trying to push for something,

445
00:26:38,394 --> 00:26:40,479
and I would never

446
00:26:40,479 --> 00:26:42,276
make this hard for you.

447
00:26:42,276 --> 00:26:44,320
I honestly figured

448
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:46,406
you were rambling because of the medication

449
00:26:46,406 --> 00:26:48,826
and being barely awake.

450
00:26:50,031 --> 00:26:53,476
Pretending I don't feel anything

451
00:26:53,476 --> 00:26:54,827
and just letting it slide,

452
00:26:54,827 --> 00:26:56,867
that's not something I can do.

453
00:26:56,867 --> 00:26:59,256
I'm sure it showed right away.

454
00:27:00,416 --> 00:27:02,426
So,

455
00:27:03,127 --> 00:27:05,671
let's just keep things

456
00:27:05,671 --> 00:27:08,007
the way they were.

457
00:27:08,007 --> 00:27:09,508
See?

458
00:27:09,508 --> 00:27:10,843
Woo Joo already knows

459
00:27:10,843 --> 00:27:12,477
the vibe is different.

460
00:27:13,679 --> 00:27:15,518
You're right.

461
00:27:15,518 --> 00:27:17,939
Woo Joo picks up on everything.

462
00:27:21,145 --> 00:27:23,530
Hold on, what is that?

463
00:27:25,132 --> 00:27:26,992
My bag.

464
00:27:29,984 --> 00:27:32,038
I don't like you.

465
00:28:03,145 --> 00:28:04,605
What's wrong?

466
00:28:04,605 --> 00:28:07,024
Mommy.

467
00:28:07,024 --> 00:28:08,025
Mommy.

468
00:28:08,025 --> 00:28:09,568
- Woo Joo.
- What's wrong?

469
00:28:09,568 --> 00:28:12,029
- Come to me.
- Mommy.

470
00:28:12,029 --> 00:28:13,698
Mommy.

471
00:28:13,698 --> 00:28:15,616
It's okay.

472
00:28:15,616 --> 00:28:17,459
Mommy.

473
00:28:20,166 --> 00:28:21,627
I'm late.

474
00:28:21,627 --> 00:28:23,355
My bag.

475
00:28:24,375 --> 00:28:25,751
Where's my wallet?

476
00:28:25,751 --> 00:28:27,461
It's on top of the toy shelf.

477
00:28:27,461 --> 00:28:29,095
Thanks.

478
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:34,552
ID card, phone.

479
00:28:34,552 --> 00:28:36,144
Right here.

480
00:28:37,365 --> 00:28:38,392
I'm going to be late.

481
00:28:38,392 --> 00:28:39,810
I need to run, I'll see you later.

482
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:41,738
Woo Joo, bye.

483
00:28:43,227 --> 00:28:44,945
See you later.

484
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:55,830
What are the cops doing here?

485
00:28:59,455 --> 00:29:01,036
Say hello to your teacher. Bow nicely.

486
00:29:01,036 --> 00:29:02,913
Hello, Woo Joo. Bow for me.

487
00:29:02,913 --> 00:29:04,290
Hello.

488
00:29:04,290 --> 00:29:05,082
See you later.

489
00:29:05,082 --> 00:29:06,083
Say bye.

490
00:29:06,083 --> 00:29:06,792
Bye.

491
00:29:06,792 --> 00:29:08,043
Say bye.

492
00:29:08,043 --> 00:29:09,970
Let's go.

493
00:29:15,721 --> 00:29:17,636
It's not safe to go home after dark.

494
00:29:17,636 --> 00:29:19,138
- I'm so scared.
- You've had a rough time.

495
00:29:19,138 --> 00:29:20,097
Leave it to me.

496
00:29:20,097 --> 00:29:22,385
I'll take care of it.

497
00:29:22,385 --> 00:29:24,643
Now where do I track down this sicko?

498
00:29:24,643 --> 00:29:26,479
The world's really gone crazy these days.

499
00:29:26,479 --> 00:29:28,355
I need to grab him and set him straight,

500
00:29:28,355 --> 00:29:29,440
right?

501
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:31,150
Just leave it to me, okay?

502
00:29:31,150 --> 00:29:33,360
What's going on?

503
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:36,322
Don't you know what goes on around here?

504
00:29:36,322 --> 00:29:37,823
A whole building in this area

505
00:29:37,823 --> 00:29:39,450
was cleaned out last night.

506
00:29:39,450 --> 00:29:40,826
And he specifically went after places

507
00:29:40,826 --> 00:29:41,994
where women live by themselves.

508
00:29:41,994 --> 00:29:43,704
Who in their right mind does that?

509
00:29:43,704 --> 00:29:45,456
The whole thing was planned out,

510
00:29:45,456 --> 00:29:46,999
and he dodged every camera in the area,

511
00:29:46,999 --> 00:29:47,875
so he's still on the loose.

512
00:29:47,875 --> 00:29:49,877
The word around here is

513
00:29:49,877 --> 00:29:51,378
some shady man wearing a cap

514
00:29:51,378 --> 00:29:53,930
has been spotted wandering around at night.

515
00:29:55,591 --> 00:29:57,183
A cap.

516
00:30:00,474 --> 00:30:02,765
Oh, come on.

517
00:30:02,765 --> 00:30:04,099
Make sure you tell

518
00:30:04,099 --> 00:30:05,851
your in-law to watch out at night.

519
00:30:05,851 --> 00:30:08,069
Until I get my hands on this guy.

520
00:30:09,396 --> 00:30:12,282
She's always out late, so that worries me.

521
00:30:13,072 --> 00:30:14,905
Did you notice the cops earlier?

522
00:30:14,905 --> 00:30:17,863
There was a break-in at our villa yesterday.

523
00:30:17,863 --> 00:30:19,031
Listen.

524
00:30:19,031 --> 00:30:21,283
Our villa got robbed yesterday.

525
00:30:21,283 --> 00:30:22,535
And the guy's still out there.

526
00:30:22,535 --> 00:30:23,953
Wait, a break-in?

527
00:30:23,953 --> 00:30:25,412
He targets women who live alone

528
00:30:25,412 --> 00:30:27,331
and stalks them after dark.

529
00:30:27,331 --> 00:30:29,291
That's absolutely insane.

530
00:30:29,291 --> 00:30:30,668
What is wrong with people lately?

531
00:30:30,668 --> 00:30:32,469
Seriously.

532
00:30:33,072 --> 00:30:35,467
Just get home early for the time being.

533
00:30:35,467 --> 00:30:37,562
Can you leave on time today?

534
00:30:38,592 --> 00:30:40,135
Hey.

535
00:30:40,135 --> 00:30:41,679
Who are you messaging right now?

536
00:30:41,679 --> 00:30:43,889
It's your in-law, isn't it?

537
00:30:43,889 --> 00:30:45,891
Tell me.

538
00:30:45,891 --> 00:30:48,356
Something happened again, didn't it?

539
00:30:48,356 --> 00:30:49,399
Seriously.

540
00:30:49,399 --> 00:30:53,190
You're hooked on drama, you know that?

541
00:30:53,190 --> 00:30:54,525
Focus on your lunch.

542
00:30:54,525 --> 00:30:55,818
Honestly, nothing at all?

543
00:30:55,818 --> 00:30:57,577
Nope.

544
00:31:01,907 --> 00:31:05,794
This wallpaper looks like it's coming off.

545
00:31:07,085 --> 00:31:10,082
You requested spaced-out installation.

546
00:31:10,082 --> 00:31:12,334
These tiles don't look quite right.

547
00:31:12,334 --> 00:31:15,254
Does all of this need to come out again?

548
00:31:15,254 --> 00:31:17,047
That's just the pattern. The pattern.

549
00:31:17,047 --> 00:31:18,765
Right, the pattern.

550
00:31:20,885 --> 00:31:22,720
The wiring is safe to use now, right?

551
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,513
Is the moisture from the pipe that burst

552
00:31:24,513 --> 00:31:26,599
all dried up now?

553
00:31:26,599 --> 00:31:28,187
I'm losing my patience here, really.

554
00:31:28,187 --> 00:31:30,936
If something needs to be fixed again,

555
00:31:30,936 --> 00:31:32,438
just let me know.

556
00:31:32,438 --> 00:31:33,564
Alright, fine.

557
00:31:33,564 --> 00:31:35,566
The tiles can be replaced,

558
00:31:35,566 --> 00:31:37,067
but there's an additional charge.

559
00:31:37,067 --> 00:31:38,611
Maybe you should've decided from the start.

560
00:31:38,611 --> 00:31:40,244
Why do you keep changing your mind?

561
00:31:40,244 --> 00:31:42,221
Want us to redo them or not?

562
00:31:43,077 --> 00:31:44,783
Things have been uneasy at the villa too,

563
00:31:44,783 --> 00:31:47,494
so now isn't ideal for moving back.

564
00:31:47,494 --> 00:31:48,621
Well, okay then.

565
00:31:48,621 --> 00:31:50,831
Decide what you want and call me.

566
00:31:50,831 --> 00:31:52,424
Come on, let's head out.

567
00:32:01,679 --> 00:32:04,524
Did this place always feel this bare?

568
00:32:27,785 --> 00:32:28,900
Hello?

569
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:29,957
Where are you?

570
00:32:29,957 --> 00:32:31,314
Shouldn't you be off the bus by now?

571
00:32:31,314 --> 00:32:33,707
I dozed off without meaning to.

572
00:32:33,707 --> 00:32:36,085
This is why you shouldn't
just fall asleep anywhere.

573
00:32:36,085 --> 00:32:37,503
Wait...

574
00:32:37,503 --> 00:32:39,713
You weren't waiting for me, right?

575
00:32:39,713 --> 00:32:42,591
No, it's not like that.

576
00:32:42,591 --> 00:32:44,426
Bom's mom took Woo Joo along

577
00:32:44,426 --> 00:32:46,098
and said she'd feed his dinner.

578
00:32:46,098 --> 00:32:47,429
I just didn't want you to make a wasted trip.

579
00:32:47,429 --> 00:32:50,140
Yeah, she let me know as well.

580
00:32:50,140 --> 00:32:52,104
Where exactly are you?

581
00:32:52,104 --> 00:32:53,644
Just say where and I'll pick you up.

582
00:32:53,644 --> 00:32:54,523
Come on.

583
00:32:54,523 --> 00:32:56,647
I can take care of myself.

584
00:32:56,647 --> 00:32:58,490
Let's just meet back at the house.

585
00:33:12,029 --> 00:33:14,081
There was a break-in at our villa.

586
00:33:14,081 --> 00:33:17,126
He goes after women living alone

587
00:33:17,126 --> 00:33:19,344
and tails them after dark.

588
00:33:45,863 --> 00:33:47,489
Just as I thought. The next stop means

589
00:33:47,489 --> 00:33:49,290
you'd be coming this way...

590
00:33:53,203 --> 00:33:55,039
What's wrong?

591
00:33:55,039 --> 00:33:56,832
What is it? Talk to me.

592
00:33:56,832 --> 00:33:58,504
What?

593
00:33:58,504 --> 00:34:00,800
Go ahead, I'm listening.

594
00:34:03,422 --> 00:34:05,056
I'm just...

595
00:34:07,676 --> 00:34:09,686
I feel safe now.

596
00:34:16,977 --> 00:34:18,312
If this ever happens again,

597
00:34:18,312 --> 00:34:20,189
reach out to me.

598
00:34:20,189 --> 00:34:22,156
Don't go through it by yourself.

599
00:34:23,859 --> 00:34:25,410
Swear

600
00:34:26,653 --> 00:34:28,872
you'll contact me.

601
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:33,793
I'm saying this
because I really worry about you.

602
00:34:37,209 --> 00:34:38,240
Alright.

603
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:40,216
Next time, I'll definitely reach out.

604
00:34:48,892 --> 00:34:52,054
So about the work on my apartment,

605
00:34:52,054 --> 00:34:53,514
the contractor called me.

606
00:34:53,514 --> 00:34:55,398
He says everything's finished.

607
00:34:56,854 --> 00:34:59,186
Oh, is that right?

608
00:34:59,186 --> 00:35:00,371
That fast?

609
00:35:02,689 --> 00:35:05,806
So I stopped by to look it over today,

610
00:35:05,806 --> 00:35:08,028
and the wallpaper was lifting off,

611
00:35:08,028 --> 00:35:09,828
the tiles were all uneven,

612
00:35:09,828 --> 00:35:11,907
and it was still damp inside.

613
00:35:11,907 --> 00:35:14,034
What even caused that pipe to burst?

614
00:35:14,034 --> 00:35:16,495
That's what I'm saying.

615
00:35:16,495 --> 00:35:19,414
It's a mystery, honestly.

616
00:35:19,414 --> 00:35:22,084
Anyway, so...

617
00:35:22,084 --> 00:35:25,678
Looks like I'll be here a while longer.

618
00:35:27,422 --> 00:35:28,677
Yeah, of course.

619
00:35:28,677 --> 00:35:31,677
Better not to move in too quickly
and end up regretting it.

620
00:35:31,677 --> 00:35:33,353
Exactly.

621
00:35:41,540 --> 00:35:43,446
Oh, I almost forgot.

622
00:35:46,525 --> 00:35:48,402
What is this?

623
00:35:48,402 --> 00:35:49,740
It's pepper spray for safety.

624
00:35:49,740 --> 00:35:52,114
I spotted it while I was out.

625
00:35:52,114 --> 00:35:53,584
Until they find the suspect,

626
00:35:53,584 --> 00:35:55,249
keep this on you.

627
00:35:57,223 --> 00:35:58,954
Honestly, the more I get to know you,

628
00:35:58,954 --> 00:36:01,339
the more I see how caring you are.

629
00:36:02,366 --> 00:36:04,046
That's because you haven't seen enough.

630
00:36:04,046 --> 00:36:06,837
With the people I care about,

631
00:36:06,837 --> 00:36:09,263
I'm actually pretty warm.

632
00:36:11,341 --> 00:36:13,468
How does this thing work, though?

633
00:36:13,468 --> 00:36:15,554
Just flip the safety lock off

634
00:36:15,554 --> 00:36:17,188
and push down hard.

635
00:36:17,893 --> 00:36:19,603
Nothing's happening.

636
00:36:19,603 --> 00:36:21,441
Come on, let me try.

637
00:36:25,164 --> 00:36:26,273
Wait, what's wrong with it?

638
00:36:26,273 --> 00:36:28,233
See, I told you it doesn't work.

639
00:36:28,233 --> 00:36:29,909
This must be a dud, right?

640
00:36:34,660 --> 00:36:35,741
Wait, what happened?

641
00:36:35,741 --> 00:36:37,075
It sprayed right in my eyes.

642
00:36:37,075 --> 00:36:38,076
It went in your eyes?

643
00:36:38,076 --> 00:36:39,161
Oh no, what now?

644
00:36:39,161 --> 00:36:40,370
Quick, call someone.

645
00:36:40,370 --> 00:36:41,705
119.

646
00:36:41,705 --> 00:36:42,789
- 119.
- I really can't see.

647
00:36:42,789 --> 00:36:43,498
Got it.

648
00:36:43,498 --> 00:36:46,043
Which way am I facing right now?

649
00:36:46,043 --> 00:36:47,885
My eyes!

650
00:36:48,754 --> 00:36:49,883
Please.

651
00:36:49,883 --> 00:36:51,465
Stop moving for a moment.

652
00:36:51,465 --> 00:36:53,675
We have to flush it out with water.

653
00:36:53,675 --> 00:36:56,053
How did you manage to spray yourself?

654
00:36:56,053 --> 00:36:57,387
Oh wait.

655
00:36:57,387 --> 00:36:59,389
I think some got in my eye as well.

656
00:36:59,389 --> 00:37:00,394
My eyes are burning so bad.

657
00:37:00,394 --> 00:37:01,350
Come on.

658
00:37:01,350 --> 00:37:02,059
Take a seat.

659
00:37:02,059 --> 00:37:03,602
Seriously, everything is blurry.

660
00:37:03,602 --> 00:37:04,436
Okay, just relax.

661
00:37:04,436 --> 00:37:05,896
I literally cannot see right now.

662
00:37:05,896 --> 00:37:07,439
Hold on to me.

663
00:37:07,439 --> 00:37:10,199
Now, try to open your eyes.

664
00:37:31,008 --> 00:37:33,090
I don't see anything wrong.

665
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:34,341
Is it still bothering you?

666
00:37:34,341 --> 00:37:37,431
When you open my eyes this wide,
of course it hurts.

667
00:37:37,431 --> 00:37:39,179
You're not doing this on purpose, are you?

668
00:37:39,179 --> 00:37:41,810
Oh please, why would I do that?

669
00:37:41,810 --> 00:37:42,929
Just wait here.

670
00:37:42,929 --> 00:37:45,234
I'll look up whether there are side effects.

671
00:38:11,169 --> 00:38:13,088
Are you okay?

672
00:38:13,088 --> 00:38:15,348
Yeah, thanks.

673
00:38:24,436 --> 00:38:27,400
Then try seeing him as a man.

674
00:38:28,312 --> 00:38:30,113
Snap out of it.

675
00:38:34,026 --> 00:38:38,079
This spray is actually no joke.

676
00:38:42,381 --> 00:38:44,494
No, it works.

677
00:38:44,494 --> 00:38:45,746
Sure.

678
00:38:45,746 --> 00:38:48,235
Just let me know once you get here.

679
00:38:48,235 --> 00:38:49,291
What is it?

680
00:38:49,291 --> 00:38:50,412
What's going on?

681
00:38:50,412 --> 00:38:52,044
We've locked in the outside team

682
00:38:52,044 --> 00:38:54,279
for visual directing on the GloMarket project.

683
00:38:54,279 --> 00:38:55,756
It's official.

684
00:38:55,756 --> 00:38:57,090
Fortunately, we landed a deal

685
00:38:57,090 --> 00:38:58,550
with the team we wanted most,

686
00:38:58,550 --> 00:39:00,305
and we're meeting them today.

687
00:39:00,305 --> 00:39:02,021
Oh, that's wonderful.

688
00:39:02,021 --> 00:39:03,597
So who did we get?

689
00:39:03,597 --> 00:39:04,931
Well...

690
00:39:04,931 --> 00:39:08,060
I believe we secured the top name in Korea.

691
00:39:08,060 --> 00:39:10,437
You can find out in person later.

692
00:39:10,437 --> 00:39:12,651
That top name in Korea is...

693
00:39:12,651 --> 00:39:14,358
- It's an honor.
- Nice to meet you.

694
00:39:14,358 --> 00:39:16,159
Amy Choo?

695
00:39:30,248 --> 00:39:31,966
Hello.

696
00:39:33,710 --> 00:39:35,504
In-law?

697
00:39:35,504 --> 00:39:37,255
In-law?

698
00:39:37,255 --> 00:39:38,423
Wait, who?

699
00:39:38,423 --> 00:39:39,257
The two of them?

700
00:39:39,257 --> 00:39:40,144
Hang on a second.

701
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:41,843
Where have I seen him before?

702
00:39:41,843 --> 00:39:43,720
There's no way he figured out

703
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:44,946
Tae Hyung's the guy from the lobby, right?

704
00:39:44,946 --> 00:39:46,598
Wait, hold on.

705
00:39:46,598 --> 00:39:48,477
Why do I feel like I know her?

706
00:39:48,477 --> 00:39:50,943
Oh, his wife?

707
00:39:52,274 --> 00:39:53,313
Wife?

708
00:39:53,313 --> 00:39:54,815
Who? The two of them?

709
00:39:54,815 --> 00:39:56,282
What?

710
00:39:57,234 --> 00:39:58,235
No, we're not.

711
00:39:58,235 --> 00:40:00,195
No?

712
00:40:00,195 --> 00:40:01,407
Alright then.

713
00:40:01,407 --> 00:40:03,998
Why don't we dive into the meeting?

714
00:40:09,643 --> 00:40:11,335
Like we outlined in the proposal,

715
00:40:11,335 --> 00:40:14,334
GloMarket has a strong interest in K-culture.

716
00:40:14,334 --> 00:40:15,919
Which is why

717
00:40:15,919 --> 00:40:17,838
your hanbok and hanok collections

718
00:40:17,838 --> 00:40:19,110
also stood out to them.

719
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:21,216
It's been some time
since I did anything Korean,

720
00:40:21,216 --> 00:40:22,884
so this could be interesting.

721
00:40:22,884 --> 00:40:24,845
And I've never shot food before,

722
00:40:24,845 --> 00:40:26,225
so that adds to the appeal.

723
00:40:26,225 --> 00:40:28,894
I get the general direction you're aiming for,

724
00:40:28,894 --> 00:40:30,517
but the visual shifts so much

725
00:40:30,517 --> 00:40:32,436
depending on each product...

726
00:40:32,436 --> 00:40:35,856
We'll nail that down on our side soon
and send it your way.

727
00:40:35,856 --> 00:40:38,108
Was there anything else you wanted to...

728
00:40:38,108 --> 00:40:40,326
Oh, it's not really a question.

729
00:40:41,126 --> 00:40:43,663
I prepared something ahead of time.

730
00:40:44,290 --> 00:40:45,327
What's this?

731
00:40:45,327 --> 00:40:47,190
Since the concept is still being decided,

732
00:40:47,190 --> 00:40:48,869
I compiled some visual references

733
00:40:48,869 --> 00:40:49,623
that match the tone

734
00:40:49,623 --> 00:40:51,621
of the images used in the proposal.

735
00:40:51,621 --> 00:40:52,876
I thought

736
00:40:52,876 --> 00:40:54,553
it might come in handy.

737
00:40:54,553 --> 00:40:55,796
This is impressive.

738
00:40:55,796 --> 00:40:57,842
We'll definitely use this.

739
00:40:58,879 --> 00:41:01,089
You know what,

740
00:41:01,089 --> 00:41:02,094
since this is our first project together,

741
00:41:02,094 --> 00:41:04,342
why don't we do a group dinner?

742
00:41:04,342 --> 00:41:05,135
Gyu Jeong,

743
00:41:05,135 --> 00:41:07,762
now that's a solid suggestion for once.

744
00:41:07,762 --> 00:41:09,931
So we're all in, then?

745
00:41:09,931 --> 00:41:11,516
I'll have to pass.

746
00:41:11,516 --> 00:41:13,435
I honestly never understood people

747
00:41:13,435 --> 00:41:15,486
who like company dinners.

748
00:41:17,043 --> 00:41:20,275
Then let's just have whoever's interested
get a bite together.

749
00:41:20,275 --> 00:41:21,318
Sounds perfect.

750
00:41:21,318 --> 00:41:23,452
I'm a huge fan of team dinners.

751
00:41:30,952 --> 00:41:34,046
That face is definitely familiar.

752
00:41:38,710 --> 00:41:40,386
Let's all get in.

753
00:41:56,353 --> 00:41:58,988
What are you looking at me for...

754
00:42:02,446 --> 00:42:04,281
Honey, how was your interview?

755
00:42:04,281 --> 00:42:07,453
Thanks to you,
everyone calls me the lobby girl.

756
00:42:08,892 --> 00:42:10,269
We're on the lobby level.

757
00:42:10,269 --> 00:42:11,330
Lobby.

758
00:42:11,330 --> 00:42:12,331
The lobby guy!

759
00:42:12,331 --> 00:42:13,411
Lobby?

760
00:42:13,411 --> 00:42:15,330
Right? That nightmare lobby guy.

761
00:42:15,330 --> 00:42:16,164
Lobby.

762
00:42:16,164 --> 00:42:18,959
- The one calling a woman "babe."
- Lobby guy!

763
00:42:18,959 --> 00:42:20,377
- The lobby guy.
- Lobby guy.

764
00:42:20,377 --> 00:42:22,462
Oh my, so then?

765
00:42:22,462 --> 00:42:24,388
She's that girl.

766
00:42:26,424 --> 00:42:27,425
It's definitely her.

767
00:42:27,425 --> 00:42:29,435
Let me out, please, open up.

768
00:42:33,143 --> 00:42:35,913
So the lobby girl
was actually you, Hyun Jin, all along.

769
00:42:35,913 --> 00:42:39,208
I had a feeling something was weird.

770
00:42:39,208 --> 00:42:41,710
Wait, are you two husband and wife?

771
00:42:41,710 --> 00:42:43,295
We told you, we're not a couple.

772
00:42:43,295 --> 00:42:44,963
If that's the case,

773
00:42:44,963 --> 00:42:46,673
then what was all that drama about?

774
00:42:46,673 --> 00:42:49,951
So you're dating then?

775
00:42:49,951 --> 00:42:50,969
Absolutely not.

776
00:42:50,969 --> 00:42:53,722
That's not it at all.

777
00:42:53,722 --> 00:42:55,516
The two of us are

778
00:42:55,516 --> 00:42:57,768
just in-laws. That's it.

779
00:42:57,768 --> 00:42:59,186
- In-laws?
- What?

780
00:42:59,186 --> 00:43:02,289
Wait, you two are in-laws?

781
00:43:03,256 --> 00:43:05,651
So what about the child?

782
00:43:05,651 --> 00:43:08,845
Wasn't there a kid in that video?

783
00:43:08,845 --> 00:43:09,863
A nephew or something?

784
00:43:09,863 --> 00:43:11,073
But...

785
00:43:11,073 --> 00:43:13,242
In-laws don't usually call each other "babe."

786
00:43:13,242 --> 00:43:15,310
That's clearly a couple thing, right?

787
00:43:15,310 --> 00:43:18,029
Or is it still undefined?

788
00:43:18,730 --> 00:43:19,648
That's really not the situation...

789
00:43:19,648 --> 00:43:21,542
Alright, that's enough.

790
00:43:21,542 --> 00:43:24,586
We all have our own stories,
and the rest is private,

791
00:43:24,586 --> 00:43:26,004
so let's leave it alone.

792
00:43:26,004 --> 00:43:27,839
Why don't we raise our glasses instead?

793
00:43:27,839 --> 00:43:30,016
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

794
00:43:30,634 --> 00:43:32,393
Drink up.

795
00:43:47,693 --> 00:43:50,696
I'd been hoping to meet you,

796
00:43:50,696 --> 00:43:53,323
though not quite under these circumstances.

797
00:43:53,323 --> 00:43:55,367
You wanted to meet me?

798
00:43:55,367 --> 00:43:57,369
How come?

799
00:43:57,369 --> 00:43:59,121
Well...

800
00:43:59,121 --> 00:44:02,124
I wanted to ask you to keep an eye on her,

801
00:44:02,124 --> 00:44:05,586
since our Hyun Jin
is secretly a bit of a klutz.

802
00:44:05,586 --> 00:44:07,178
"Our"?

803
00:44:11,842 --> 00:44:13,684
Have some water too.

804
00:44:18,481 --> 00:44:19,833
Yes.

805
00:44:19,833 --> 00:44:23,729
Honestly, since when am I a klutz?

806
00:44:23,729 --> 00:44:24,813
Oh, come on.

807
00:44:24,813 --> 00:44:26,315
Think back to our college days.

808
00:44:26,315 --> 00:44:27,691
Back then, you would...

809
00:44:27,691 --> 00:44:31,445
That's so unfair, using old stories.

810
00:44:31,445 --> 00:44:33,363
Oh, by the way,

811
00:44:33,363 --> 00:44:35,407
neither of you had any idea?

812
00:44:35,407 --> 00:44:37,326
That you'd end up on the same project.

813
00:44:37,326 --> 00:44:38,327
No.

814
00:44:38,327 --> 00:44:41,086
I honestly didn't know at all.

815
00:44:41,086 --> 00:44:43,305
Did you know?

816
00:44:43,305 --> 00:44:44,357
What?

817
00:44:44,357 --> 00:44:46,209
Why did you keep it to yourself?

818
00:44:46,209 --> 00:44:47,919
Well, I guess,

819
00:44:47,919 --> 00:44:50,088
just because you share a place

820
00:44:50,088 --> 00:44:52,007
doesn't mean you share everything.

821
00:44:52,007 --> 00:44:53,759
We are close, actually.

822
00:44:53,759 --> 00:44:56,136
Ah, I see.

823
00:44:56,136 --> 00:44:58,138
You probably have no idea

824
00:44:58,138 --> 00:45:01,058
about her personal relationships

825
00:45:01,058 --> 00:45:03,985
given that you're only her supervisor.

826
00:45:04,853 --> 00:45:06,855
By the way...

827
00:45:06,855 --> 00:45:09,566
It's unbelievable how people
come up with these wild stories.

828
00:45:09,566 --> 00:45:11,742
"Lobby guy," seriously.

829
00:45:13,195 --> 00:45:14,988
You're not her boyfriend.

830
00:45:14,988 --> 00:45:16,789
You're her family member.

831
00:45:23,288 --> 00:45:25,123
Let's not just sit here like this.

832
00:45:25,123 --> 00:45:26,375
Let's toast, come on.

833
00:45:26,375 --> 00:45:28,168
Hold on.

834
00:45:28,168 --> 00:45:29,886
There's something on your lips.

835
00:45:36,093 --> 00:45:37,302
Did you spill?

836
00:45:37,302 --> 00:45:39,596
Watch what you're doing.

837
00:45:39,596 --> 00:45:42,015
You've been off since yesterday, what's up?

838
00:45:42,015 --> 00:45:44,358
Was I too intense yesterday?

839
00:45:47,270 --> 00:45:49,439
Well...

840
00:45:49,439 --> 00:45:51,358
Did something go down yesterday?

841
00:45:51,358 --> 00:45:53,694
It's just, yesterday he had

842
00:45:53,694 --> 00:45:55,362
a thing with pepper spray.

843
00:45:55,362 --> 00:45:57,114
Pepper spray?

844
00:45:57,114 --> 00:45:58,615
Why, what happened?

845
00:45:58,615 --> 00:46:00,350
Was there another incident?

846
00:46:00,350 --> 00:46:03,912
There was a burglary at the villa,
and yesterday was absolute madness.

847
00:46:03,912 --> 00:46:05,872
A burglary?

848
00:46:05,872 --> 00:46:07,548
You're alright, though?

849
00:46:08,441 --> 00:46:11,287
Yooseong Villa's security
must be really lacking.

850
00:46:11,287 --> 00:46:12,295
I'm alright.

851
00:46:12,295 --> 00:46:13,797
Tae Hyung's there with me,

852
00:46:13,797 --> 00:46:14,965
so there's nothing to worry about.

853
00:46:14,965 --> 00:46:17,134
Don't worry. I'm home with her.

854
00:46:17,134 --> 00:46:20,554
She's not exactly like Suzy,
despite how she looks.

855
00:46:21,423 --> 00:46:23,356
Cut it out.

856
00:46:24,307 --> 00:46:26,877
Why are you nudging me

857
00:46:26,877 --> 00:46:29,966
with your foot under the table?

858
00:46:38,608 --> 00:46:39,948
Everything's just clicking today.

859
00:46:39,948 --> 00:46:41,908
Strike.

860
00:46:41,908 --> 00:46:43,493
I forgot how much fun this is.

861
00:46:43,493 --> 00:46:46,170
How about you two face off?

862
00:46:47,164 --> 00:46:49,340
Sun Tae Hyung.

863
00:47:07,225 --> 00:47:09,895
Your in-law is quite the catch, huh?

864
00:47:09,895 --> 00:47:12,105
I'm sorry?

865
00:47:12,105 --> 00:47:13,565
People like him that much?

866
00:47:13,565 --> 00:47:17,319
Regardless, they're both eye candy.

867
00:47:17,319 --> 00:47:19,613
Is he really that handsome?

868
00:47:19,613 --> 00:47:21,114
Which one's your type?

869
00:47:21,114 --> 00:47:22,407
Manager Park?

870
00:47:22,407 --> 00:47:24,618
Or your in-law?

871
00:47:24,618 --> 00:47:25,577
Manager, show us what you've got.

872
00:47:25,577 --> 00:47:27,461
Oh, our manager.

873
00:47:43,011 --> 00:47:44,221
Nice one, Tae Hyung.

874
00:47:44,221 --> 00:47:47,815
You're really good.

875
00:48:13,875 --> 00:48:15,794
So close.

876
00:48:15,794 --> 00:48:17,428
That was really close.

877
00:48:31,434 --> 00:48:33,395
That's it!

878
00:48:33,395 --> 00:48:34,521
Sun Tae Hyung.

879
00:48:34,521 --> 00:48:36,489
There you go.

880
00:48:37,107 --> 00:48:38,949
Come on, Tae Hyung.

881
00:48:40,902 --> 00:48:42,912
You've got this, Manager.

882
00:48:44,072 --> 00:48:47,333
- Manager, you got this.
- You got this.

883
00:48:53,164 --> 00:48:56,626
As expected!

884
00:48:56,626 --> 00:48:58,886
Those veins are looking sharp.

885
00:49:01,298 --> 00:49:03,066
You're the best.

886
00:49:07,929 --> 00:49:09,472
Not bad at all.

887
00:49:09,472 --> 00:49:11,349
It's your final throw.

888
00:49:11,349 --> 00:49:13,609
It's not over yet.

889
00:49:14,335 --> 00:49:17,474
It's not finished until the last frame.

890
00:49:46,885 --> 00:49:48,470
Hey, Manager.

891
00:49:48,470 --> 00:49:52,265
It's such a shame you lost tonight.

892
00:49:52,265 --> 00:49:54,392
How about just one more round, please?

893
00:49:54,392 --> 00:49:56,127
Have a safe trip home.

894
00:49:56,127 --> 00:49:57,420
- Good night.
- Hey, Tae Hyung.

895
00:49:57,420 --> 00:49:59,567
I need you to come by the studio with me.

896
00:49:59,567 --> 00:50:00,607
At this hour?

897
00:50:00,607 --> 00:50:02,067
Yeah, something came up with a shoot.

898
00:50:02,067 --> 00:50:04,569
I already got a cab, so let's take it.

899
00:50:04,569 --> 00:50:05,904
I can drive you home.

900
00:50:05,904 --> 00:50:06,988
Ride with me.

901
00:50:06,988 --> 00:50:07,864
Would that be okay?

902
00:50:07,864 --> 00:50:08,615
Wait, I could...

903
00:50:08,615 --> 00:50:09,491
Did you call for a driver?

904
00:50:09,491 --> 00:50:11,368
- Oh, yes, that one.
- Oh, this one? Yes.

905
00:50:11,368 --> 00:50:13,787
- Let's go.
- Okay.

906
00:50:13,787 --> 00:50:15,463
I'll see you later.

907
00:50:17,582 --> 00:50:19,341
Seriously...

908
00:50:21,878 --> 00:50:24,972
You're actually riding with him?

909
00:50:26,341 --> 00:50:29,302
He and I are headed the same way.

910
00:50:29,302 --> 00:50:31,089
What's wrong?

911
00:50:31,930 --> 00:50:33,431
Our cab just pulled up.

912
00:50:33,431 --> 00:50:35,183
I'll see you next time then.

913
00:50:35,183 --> 00:50:36,726
Get home safe.

914
00:50:36,726 --> 00:50:38,520
Unless we're in a rush,
let me hit the restroom.

915
00:50:38,520 --> 00:50:40,355
Forget the restroom, just get in the cab.

916
00:50:40,355 --> 00:50:42,857
Oh, come on.

917
00:50:42,857 --> 00:50:43,942
Yeah, we're leaving.

918
00:50:43,942 --> 00:50:45,068
Just get in already.

919
00:50:45,068 --> 00:50:46,236
I can't deal with you.

920
00:50:46,236 --> 00:50:47,828
Get in.

921
00:50:57,831 --> 00:51:00,466
It's written all over your face, you know.

922
00:51:01,793 --> 00:51:03,169
What do you mean?

923
00:51:03,169 --> 00:51:04,170
So what's your plan?

924
00:51:04,170 --> 00:51:07,298
Your rival looks pretty tough.

925
00:51:07,298 --> 00:51:09,551
It's not like that.

926
00:51:09,551 --> 00:51:11,511
Love isn't something you compete for.

927
00:51:11,511 --> 00:51:14,347
In my experience,

928
00:51:14,347 --> 00:51:16,766
everything else is irrelevant.

929
00:51:16,766 --> 00:51:19,193
There's only one thing that counts in love.

930
00:51:21,980 --> 00:51:23,739
What's that?

931
00:51:24,607 --> 00:51:26,192
Timing.

932
00:51:26,192 --> 00:51:28,278
If you miss the right moment,

933
00:51:28,278 --> 00:51:30,488
nothing you do will make a difference.

934
00:51:30,488 --> 00:51:32,866
Take me, for example.

935
00:51:32,866 --> 00:51:35,952
I waited too long to make things right,

936
00:51:35,952 --> 00:51:38,288
and next thing I knew, it was over.

937
00:51:38,288 --> 00:51:40,089
Well...

938
00:51:41,249 --> 00:51:43,960
I think you still have a chance,

939
00:51:43,960 --> 00:51:47,088
but you keep missing it.

940
00:51:47,088 --> 00:51:48,644
Hold on, you knew this whole time?

941
00:51:48,644 --> 00:51:49,382
That Amy Choo and I...

942
00:51:49,382 --> 00:51:51,259
That you guys are married?

943
00:51:51,259 --> 00:51:53,511
You two argue at full volume every day.

944
00:51:53,511 --> 00:51:56,139
It's hard to miss.

945
00:51:56,139 --> 00:51:58,774
Was I really that loud?

946
00:51:59,559 --> 00:52:01,895
I'll try to lower my voice from now on.

947
00:52:01,895 --> 00:52:04,481
Sun Tae Hyung, can you hear me?

948
00:52:04,481 --> 00:52:06,240
I can hear you perfectly.

949
00:52:30,531 --> 00:52:31,549
Thank you.

950
00:52:31,549 --> 00:52:33,225
Thank you.

951
00:52:35,678 --> 00:52:37,705
Feeling alright?

952
00:52:37,705 --> 00:52:38,723
I'm okay.

953
00:52:38,723 --> 00:52:42,817
The breeze is making me feel better.

954
00:52:42,817 --> 00:52:45,396
Let's stay and cool off for a bit.

955
00:52:45,396 --> 00:52:48,650
There's no way we'll find a driver right now.

956
00:52:48,650 --> 00:52:50,276
How come?

957
00:52:50,276 --> 00:52:52,995
They're setting off fireworks
around here tonight.

958
00:53:08,128 --> 00:53:09,845
Woo Hyun Jin.

959
00:53:10,547 --> 00:53:12,640
Want to go watch the fireworks?

960
00:53:14,801 --> 00:53:18,304
Do you want to go look at flowers?

961
00:53:18,304 --> 00:53:19,389
Hey.

962
00:53:19,389 --> 00:53:21,141
Let's go, I brought the car.

963
00:53:21,141 --> 00:53:23,560
There are fireworks at the Han River tonight.

964
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:25,527
Seriously?

965
00:53:37,991 --> 00:53:39,708
Thank you.

966
00:53:41,911 --> 00:53:44,330
We're finally seeing the fireworks

967
00:53:44,330 --> 00:53:46,006
we missed seven years ago.

968
00:53:48,168 --> 00:53:49,927
Right.

969
00:53:52,213 --> 00:53:55,133
You must have been so thrown off back then.

970
00:53:55,133 --> 00:53:57,810
The way I took off without warning.

971
00:54:00,471 --> 00:54:02,314
Are you serious?

972
00:54:03,391 --> 00:54:04,459
He gave up

973
00:54:04,459 --> 00:54:07,170
the scholarship for me?

974
00:54:07,170 --> 00:54:08,188
No.

975
00:54:08,188 --> 00:54:10,489
Please don't handle it that way.

976
00:54:19,824 --> 00:54:21,375
Yoon Seong.

977
00:54:22,785 --> 00:54:25,587
I told you earlier I had something to say.

978
00:54:26,873 --> 00:54:28,841
Actually...

979
00:54:31,544 --> 00:54:33,554
I'm leaving soon for a language program.

980
00:54:37,175 --> 00:54:39,143
So...

981
00:54:41,930 --> 00:54:43,939
I don't think we can see each other anymore.

982
00:54:53,191 --> 00:54:58,120
I walked away and left you behind.

983
00:55:00,156 --> 00:55:03,201
Now I think I know

984
00:55:03,201 --> 00:55:05,878
how you must have felt.

985
00:55:08,790 --> 00:55:10,416
At least back then,

986
00:55:10,416 --> 00:55:13,461
the traffic was so horrible that

987
00:55:13,461 --> 00:55:16,092
it wasn't as miserable as you'd think.

988
00:55:21,052 --> 00:55:22,720
Now that I think about it,

989
00:55:22,720 --> 00:55:25,522
you had your own car even then.

990
00:55:28,643 --> 00:55:31,070
That's why I turned you down.

991
00:55:32,021 --> 00:55:34,983
I lived in a semi-basement back then.

992
00:55:34,983 --> 00:55:39,161
So when I heard
you'd give up your scholarship for me,

993
00:55:40,071 --> 00:55:44,367
I figured you'd seen how broke I was.

994
00:55:44,367 --> 00:55:47,161
So I made up a lie.

995
00:55:47,161 --> 00:55:49,463
All because of my stupid pride.

996
00:55:54,752 --> 00:55:55,920
Wait.

997
00:55:55,920 --> 00:55:58,180
You already knew everything.

998
00:55:59,257 --> 00:56:02,010
Why didn't you just say so?

999
00:56:02,010 --> 00:56:03,936
Now I look like a fool.

1000
00:56:04,971 --> 00:56:07,397
To be honest, I was afraid too.

1001
00:56:08,474 --> 00:56:11,401
I worried you'd pull away if you found out.

1002
00:56:16,024 --> 00:56:18,659
I didn't think anything scared you.

1003
00:56:21,696 --> 00:56:23,573
More than you'd think.

1004
00:56:23,573 --> 00:56:26,542
But it's mostly about one thing in particular.

1005
00:56:28,911 --> 00:56:30,546
You.

1006
00:56:36,002 --> 00:56:38,212
Anyway,

1007
00:56:38,212 --> 00:56:41,007
I'm glad I finally said it.

1008
00:56:41,007 --> 00:56:43,225
Even though it's kind of humiliating.

1009
00:56:45,845 --> 00:56:47,521
Thank you

1010
00:56:49,599 --> 00:56:51,817
for bringing it up first.

1011
00:57:00,276 --> 00:57:02,244
Look how big that one is.

1012
00:57:02,862 --> 00:57:04,663
It's beautiful.

1013
00:57:21,498 --> 00:57:22,823
Thank you.

1014
00:57:22,823 --> 00:57:23,841
Thanks.

1015
00:57:23,841 --> 00:57:26,101
I'll wait until you get inside.

1016
00:57:32,517 --> 00:57:34,352
Take care on your way back.

1017
00:57:34,352 --> 00:57:35,944
Will do.

1018
00:57:43,778 --> 00:57:45,071
It's me.

1019
00:57:45,071 --> 00:57:46,948
Yeah.

1020
00:57:46,948 --> 00:57:48,449
Are you home yet?

1021
00:57:48,449 --> 00:57:50,618
I'm almost there.

1022
00:57:50,618 --> 00:57:51,911
When are you coming home?

1023
00:57:51,911 --> 00:57:53,955
I'll leave in a minute.

1024
00:57:53,955 --> 00:57:55,331
I just wanted to make sure

1025
00:57:55,331 --> 00:57:57,591
you made it back okay.

1026
00:58:03,423 --> 00:58:05,474
I was just about to call you...

1027
00:58:07,218 --> 00:58:09,262
What?

1028
00:58:09,262 --> 00:58:10,896
What's wrong?

1029
00:58:12,640 --> 00:58:14,475
Hello?

1030
00:58:14,475 --> 00:58:17,945
The front door is open...

1031
00:58:20,047 --> 00:58:22,191
Did I leave it unlocked when I went out?

1032
00:58:22,191 --> 00:58:24,743
No, I know I shut it before I left...

1033
00:58:46,340 --> 00:58:48,130
Woo Hyun Jin.

1034
00:59:31,614 --> 00:59:33,920
What in the world is going on?

1035
00:59:34,580 --> 00:59:36,655
Are you okay? Tell me you're not hurt.

1036
00:59:36,655 --> 00:59:38,697
Please make sure
she doesn't get into any danger

1037
00:59:38,697 --> 00:59:40,113
because of you.

1038
00:59:40,113 --> 00:59:41,987
If something happens to her,

1039
00:59:41,987 --> 00:59:43,872
make sure to tell me.

1040
00:59:44,863 --> 00:59:46,739
Apparently the one who stole data

1041
00:59:46,739 --> 00:59:48,988
is a temp on that team.

1042
00:59:48,988 --> 00:59:50,429
What? Have they lost their minds?

1043
00:59:50,429 --> 00:59:53,655
Blaming someone with no evidence is harassment.

1044
00:59:53,655 --> 00:59:56,435
Once this project wraps up, let's go on a date.

1045
00:59:56,435 --> 00:59:57,988
Hyun Jin, do you still

1046
00:59:57,988 --> 01:00:00,155
have feelings for Manager Park?
